      <akn:section eId="sec_28:2A_407">
        <akn:num>28:2A-407</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Irrevocable promises: finance leases.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-407_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>In the case of a finance lease that is not a consumer lease, the lessee’s promises under the lease contract become irrevocable and independent upon the lessee’s acceptance of the goods.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-407_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A promise that has become irrevocable and independent under subsection (a) of this section:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-407_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>This section does not affect the validity under any other law of a covenant in any lease contract making the lessee’s promises irrevocable and independent upon the lessee’s acceptance of the goods.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
